The paper focuses on learning short binary codes for fast information retrieval, which is a common topic in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also builds on the work of Le & Mikolov, who are well-known for their contributions to natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the precision of binary codes in transfer learning settings, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
